  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Local Cooperation Fund (LCF) in Mexico</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project continues the work started in 2009 in a project, which aimed at promoting the sustainable use of forests and prevent the loss of forests in the indigenous area of Mazahua in the state Estado de Mexico. Within the project 160 firewood saving stoves are built in Mazahua households and an area of 100 hectares are reforested. Workshops on the protection of environment are organized and the participation of women in particular is encouraged. The project benefits four groups of indigenous peoples and lasts for a year.</narrative>
  </description>
